bial interactions can promote the health of beneficial insects, especially in the context of environmental pollutants and climate change.Insects and Their Beneficial Microbes provides a much-needed conceptual framework for the growing discipline of insect-microbial interactions, and offers a wealth of insights into insect symbioses from molecular, physiological, ecological, and evolutionary perspectives.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aBacteria. 0aInsectsxMolecular aspects. 0aMicroorganisms. 0aSymbiosis. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Microbiology.2bisacsh  amicroorganisms, entomological, insect microbiomes, cells of insects, insect pests, insect habitats, bacteriocyte, beneficial microbe, ectosymbiosis, gut microbiome, insect, microbiome, symbiosis, Wolbachia, insect-microbial, insect microbial interactions.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2022 Englishz978311099319608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2022z9783110993134oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311074973140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978069123623040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691236230423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691236230/original  a978-3-11-074973-1  Princeton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099319-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_